-- Indonesian Stock Movers: Astra Otoparts, Energi Mega Persada
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-04-20T05:14:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/indonesian-stock-movers-astra-otoparts-energi-mega-persada.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11:30 a.m. Jakarta-time
break. The  Jakarta Composite Index (JCI)  rose 0.18 points, or less
than 0.1 percent, to 4,163.89. The gauge has added 0.1 percent
this week.  PT Astra Otoparts (AUTO)  , a car and motorcycle parts
maker, rose 1.5 percent to 3,475 rupiah. The company plans to
spend 1.6 trillion rupiah ($175 million) on capital expenditure
this year to add new products and increase capacity, Bisnis
Indonesia reported, citing President Director Siswanto
Prawiroatmodjo. Astra plans to build a factory in Karawang, West
Java province and set up a joint venture with Italian tire
producer Pirelli & C. SpA, the report said. Two calls to the
company’s office weren’t answered.  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  , Indonesia’s second-
biggest listed oil company, gained 3.6 percent to 200 rupiah,
heading for the highest close since Feb. 1. The company expects
to start producing oil from its Tonga Block in North Sumatra
province at a rate of 1,200 barrels a day in the first half of
this year, Energi Mega said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
